parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in the repair, leaving the vehicle unsafe to drive and increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None
as this is a recall-related issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can increase the risk of injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident
even when the impact is severe enough to warrant deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries to the occupants and lead to a loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
causing injuries to the occupants and potentially leading to a loss of control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard illuminates
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse gear can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or become stuck, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: The vehicle won't go into reverse
the engine revs up when in reverse gear
the shift lever seems to be working but the vehicle doesn't move in reverse
the indicator on the dashboard says "R" but the vehicle doesn't move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or become stuck, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: The vehicle won't go into gear
the engine revs up when in gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential mounts can cause the vehicle to vibrate or make loud noises, leading to loss of control or accidents, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud clunking noise
the vehicle vibrates when driving
the differential mounts are torn or cracked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation or failure of the rear subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries. This issue can also lead to noisy and misaligned suspension parts, which can further compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Creaking noise coming from the rear suspension
stress fractures and separations at the point where the mount is welded to the unibody
noisy and misaligned suspension parts
vibration while braking
loss of vehicle control.

stress fractures and separations at the point where the mount is welded to the unibody
noisy and misaligned suspension parts.
